	<h1> My Favorite Recipe </h1> <br>
	<p>Hello everyone! Now that summer is here, and it has been very warm outside,
  I don't like to cook. The following recipe is one of my summer favorites.
  I hope you enjoy it too!</p> <br>
  <h2>Easy Caprese Salad</h2>
<h3>Ingredients:</h3>
<ul> 3 tomatoes (1/4-inch thick slices), 1 lb. Fresh Mozzarella (1/4-inch thick slices),
1 bunch Fresh Basil, Extra-Virgin Olive Oil, Coarse Salt and Pepper</ul>
<h2>Directions:</h2>
<ul>
     <li> Layer alternating slices of tomatoes and mozzarella on a large platter.</li>
              <ol>
                  <li>diagonally, as you would a meat and cheese tray</li>
              </ol>
     <li> Add a basil leaf between each layer of the tomato and cheese.</li>
     <li> Drizzle the salad with extra-virgin olive oil. </li>
     <li> Season salad with salt and pepper to taste.</li>

